HEADWORD: Archiepiscopacy
<hw>Ar`chi*e*pis"co*pa*cy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>archi-</ets> + <ets>episcopacy</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
form of episcopacy in which the chief power is in the hands of
archbishops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state or dignity of an archbishop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Archiepiscopal</ent>⟦br⟧
